<!-- PJG ITAG l=95 g=1 f=4 -->
Summary of Proposed NSPS for New MWC's 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=96 g=1 f=4 -->
[Subpart Eb]
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=96 g=5 f=1 -->
a 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=96 g=1 f=1 -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 007 0150 intable -->
1Plant size (MSW combustion capacity) 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 007 0150 intable -->
1Requirement
<!-- PJG 007 0152 intable -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=2 -->
Applicability
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG QTAG 03 -->
<!-- PJG /QTAG -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=2 -->
The proposed NSPS would apply to new MWC units located at plants with capacities to combust greater than 25 Mg/day of
residential, commercial, and/or institutional discards.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=5 f=1 -->
b
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 Industrial discards are not covered by the proposed NSPS.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG QTAG 03 -->
<!-- PJG /QTAG -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=03 g=1 f=1 -->
&lt;25 Mg/day 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 007 0104 intable -->
Not covered by standards.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
>25 Mg/day but &lt; 35 Mg/day 
<!-- PJG 007 0104 intable -->
Initial report of MWC design capacity and startup date.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
>35 Mg/day but &lt; 225 Mg/day (referred to 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
as small MWC plants)
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 007 0104 intable -->
Subject to provisions listed below.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
>225 Mg/day (referred to 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
as large MWC plants)
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 007 0104 intable -->
Subject to provisions listed below.
