<!-- PJG ITAG l=22 g=1 f=1 -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=22 g=1 f=2 -->
Good Combustion Practices:
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=12 g=1 f=2 -->
&bull;Applies to large and small MWC plants. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
&bull;A site-specific operator training manual would be required to be developed and made available for MWC personnel.
The EPA or State MWC operator training course would be required to be completed by the MWC chief facility operator,
shift supervisors, and control room operators. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
&bull;The ASME or a State MWC operator certification would be required to be obtained by the MWC chief facility operator
(mandatory), shift supervisors (mandatory), and control room operators (optional). 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
&bull;The MWC load level would be required to be measured and not to exceed the maximum load level as demonstrated during
the most recent dioxin/furan performance test. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
&bull;The PM control device inlet flue gas temperature would be required to be measured and not to exceed the level
demonstrated during the most recent dioxin/furan performance test. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
&bull;The CO level would be required to be measured using CEMS, and the concentration in the flue gas would be required
not to exceed the following.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

